# Role Add Flow:

01. User Role form (RoleView.jsp) par Name aur Description fill karta hai aur Save button par click karta hai.

02. Form submit hone par request RoleCtl par jati hai.

03. Sabse pehle BaseCtl ki service() method call hoti hai.

04. service() method me operation parameter nikala jata hai.

05. Agar operation SAVE hai aur CANCEL/RESET/VIEW/DELETE nahi hai tab validate(request) method call hota hai.

06. validate() method (RoleCtl me override) call hota hai:
    - name null check
    - name format check
    - description null check

07. Agar validation fail hoti hai to:
    - request.setAttribute() me error message set hota hai
    - request wapas RoleView.jsp par forward ho jati hai

08. Agar validation pass ho jati hai to control RoleCtl ke doPost() method me jata hai.

09. doPost() method me operation check hota hai:
    if (OP_SAVE.equalsIgnoreCase(op))

10. populateBean(request) call hota hai aur RoleBean object create hota hai jisme:
    - id
    - name
    - description
    - createdBy, modifiedBy
    - createdDatetime, modifiedDatetime set hote hain

11. RoleModel ka object banaya jata hai:
    RoleModel model = new RoleModel();

12. model.add(bean) method call hoti hai.

13. RoleModel.add() method me:
    - findByName(bean.getName()) call hoti hai (duplicate check)

14. Agar same role name already exist karta hai to:
    - DuplicateRecordException throw hoti hai

15. Agar duplicate nahi milta:
    - nextPk() se next id generate hoti hai
    - database connection liya jata hai
    - autoCommit false kiya jata hai

16. PreparedStatement banakar query execute hoti hai:
    insert into st_role values(...)

17. pstmt.executeUpdate() call hota hai aur record database me insert ho jata hai.

18. conn.commit() call hota hai aur transaction complete ho jata hai.

19. Control wapas RoleCtl ke doPost() me aata hai.

20. ServletUtility.setBean(bean, request) call hota hai.

21. ServletUtility.setSuccessMessage("Data is successfully saved", request) set kiya jata hai.

22. Agar DuplicateRecordException aati hai to:
    - ServletUtility.setErrorMessage("Role already exists", request) set hota hai

23. Last me:
    ServletUtility.forward(getView(), request, response) call hota hai.

24. Request wapas RoleView.jsp par forward hoti hai.

25. JSP par:
    - Success ya Error message display hota hai
    - Input values dubara show hoti hain
